## How AI tooling is wired

This project uses the **`ai-specs`** standard. The manifest at
`ai-specs/ai-specs.toml` declares enabled agents, vendored skills, and MCP
servers. Per-agent configs live under each agent's directory (`.claude/`,
`.cursor/`, etc.) and are **generated** from the manifest — do not hand-edit.

To regenerate after changing `ai-specs.toml`:

```bash
./ai-specs/cli/ai-specs sync   # init + sync-agent --all
```

To add a skill:

```bash
./ai-specs/cli/ai-specs add-skill <name>          # local skill (this repo)
./ai-specs/cli/ai-specs add-dep <git-url>         # vendored skill (external)
```

